   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "# counts over industries (transpose)\n",
    "IE_entp = data[data[\"FINAL_IE\"] == \"C\"]\n",
    "# order = IE_entp[\"CLUSTER_DEFN\"].value_counts().index\n",
    "# Get the unique cluster definitions and sort them alphabetically\n",
    "order = sorted(IE_entp[\"CLUSTER_DEFN\"].unique())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a countplot with counts on the bars\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(16, 12))\n",
    "ax = sns.countplot(y=\"CLUSTER_DEFN\", data=IE_entp, hue=\"REF_YR\", palette=\"viridis\", order=order)\n",
    "\n",
    "for p in ax.patches:\n",
    "    ax.text(p.get_width() + 1, p.get_y() + p.get_height() / 2., \n",
    "            int(p.get_width()), \n",
    "            fontsize=11, color='black', ha='left', va='center')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d84b8657-1433-461e-854e-37a0c3c044d1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Counts by Industry across years 2020 - 2023"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "357e539a-c2a1-4e33-9423-eda669380327",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def count_final_ie_c(df, var=None):\n",
    "    # Filter the DataFrame to include only rows where FINAL_IE is \"C\"\n",
    "    filtered_df = df.loc[(df['FINAL_IE'] == 'C')]\n",
    "    if var is not None:\n",
    "        filtered_df = df.loc[(df['FINAL_IE'] == 'C') & (df['CLUSTER_DEFN'].isin(var))]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Group by CLUSTER_DEFN and REF_YR and count the occurrences\n",
    "    count_df = filtered_df.groupby(['CLUSTER_DEFN', 'REF_YR']).size().reset_index(name='Count')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Sort the DataFrame for better readability\n",
    "    count_df = count_df.sort_values(by=['CLUSTER_DEFN', 'REF_YR']).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return count_df"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "5253a7ca-2b6d-4bd0-b306-c999cd12095a",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "def calculate_percentage_change(df):\n",
    "    # Ensure the DataFrame is sorted by CLUSTER_DEFN and REF_YR\n",
    "    df = df.sort_values(by=['CLUSTER_DEFN', 'REF_YR']).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Pivot the DataFrame to have years as columns and sectors as rows\n",
    "    pivot_df = df.pivot(index='CLUSTER_DEFN', columns='REF_YR', values='Count').fillna(0)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate the percentage change from 2020 to 2023\n",
    "    pct_change_df = pivot_df.loc[:, 2020:2023].pct_change(axis='columns') * 100\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Reset the index to make it a DataFrame again\n",
    "    pct_change_df = pct_change_df.reset_index()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return pct_change_df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "b673ed4f-d1b3-460f-9a54-bc6510203215",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pct_change = calculate_percentage_change(count_final)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "def plot_percentage_change(pct_change_df):\n",
    "    # Melt the DataFrame to long format for seaborn plotting\n",
    "    melted_df = pct_change_df.melt(id_vars='CLUSTER_DEFN', var_name='Year', value_name='Percentage Change')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Plot using seaborn\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "    sns.barplot(data=melted_df, x='Percentage Change', y='CLUSTER_DEFN', hue='Year', palette='pastel')\n",
    "    plt.title('Percentage Change Revenue-Generating Website Counts by Selected Industries (2021-2023)')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('Percentage Change (Revenue Generating Counts)')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('Sector')\n",
    "    plt.legend(title='Year')"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "#### % Change of \"Revenue-Generating\" Firm Count (2023)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "3ed0d70d-c0fb-446f-b172-9ee40186c1a1",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_percentage_change_2023(df):\n",
    "    # Ensure the DataFrame is sorted by CLUSTER_DEFN and REF_YR\n",
    "    df = df.sort_values(by=['CLUSTER_DEFN', 'REF_YR']).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Pivot the DataFrame to have years as columns and sectors as rows\n",
    "    pivot_df = df.pivot(index='CLUSTER_DEFN', columns='REF_YR', values='Count').fillna(0)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate the percentage change from 2022 to 2023\n",
    "    pct_change_series = (pivot_df[2023] - pivot_df[2022]) / pivot_df[2022] * 100\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Create a DataFrame with the results\n",
    "    pct_change_df = pct_change_series.to_frame(name='pct_change2023').reset_index()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return pct_change_df"
   ]
  },

    "# import flad_base\n",
    "flad_base = pd.read_sas('/nas-p1/dosfs/bsd/flad/End_User/JKYEE/IE2023/IE2022/ie2023_analysis/flad_basev1.sas7bdat', format=\"sas7bdat\", encoding=\"utf-8\")\n",
    "flad_base2022 = flad_base.loc[flad_base[\"REF_YR\"] == \"2022\"]\n",
    "df = data.loc[(data[\"REF_YR\"] == 2023)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# conver ref_yr to str\n",
    "df[\"REF_YR\"] = df[\"REF_YR\"].astype(str)\n",
    "\n",
    "# merge datasets\n",
    "merged_df = pd.merge(df, flad_base2022[['UEN', 'SSIC2020']], on=['UEN'], how='left')\n",
    "merged_df.head()"

     "execution_count": 37,

   ],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "def extract_and_filter_records(data, merged_df):\n",
    "    # Filter for FINAL_IE = \"C\" in REF_YR = \"2023\"\n",
    "    filter_2023 = data[(data['FINAL_IE'] == 'C') & (data['REF_YR'] == 2023)]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Filter for FINAL_IE = \"A\" or \"B\" in REF_YR = \"2022\"\n",
    "    filter_2022 = data[(data['FINAL_IE'].isin(['A', 'B'])) & (data['REF_YR'] == 2022)]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Merge on UEN to find common entries\n",
    "    merged = pd.merge(filter_2023, filter_2022, on='UEN', suffixes=('_2023', '_2022'))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Extract the UEN column\n",
    "    uen_list = merged['UEN'].unique()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Filter original data for those UENs\n",
    "    filtered_data = merged_df[merged_df['UEN'].isin(uen_list)]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return filtered_data\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example usage\n",
    "filtered_records = extract_and_filter_records(data, merged_df)\n",
    "filtered_records.head()"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_ssic2020_counts(filtered_records, cluster_defn_name):\n",
    "    # Filter records for the given CLUSTER_DEFN\n",
    "    cluster_records = filtered_records[filtered_records['CLUSTER_DEFN'] == cluster_defn_name]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Get value counts of SSIC2020 in descending order\n",
    "    ssic2020_counts = cluster_records['SSIC2020'].value_counts().sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return ssic2020_counts\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example usage\n",
    "cluster_name = \"19. Professional Services\"\n",
    "ssic2020_result = get_ssic2020_counts(filtered_records, cluster_name)\n",
    "ssic2020_result"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# Function to map OR_Band to OR_Band_3\n",
    "def map_or_band(band):\n",
    "    if band in ['01. OR <= 1 Million', '02. 1 Million < OR <= 10 Million']:\n",
    "        return '01-02. OR <= 10 Million'\n",
    "    return band\n",
    "\n",
    "# Creating the new OR_Band_3 variable\n",
    "df2023['OR_Band_3'] = df2023['OR_Band'].apply(map_or_band)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display the updated DataFrame\n",
    "df2023.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 150,
   "id": "0c9eb0c3-39e6-4c2e-9e66-296fb8e341bd",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1400x800 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot_website_percentage_by_revenue(df2023):\n",
    "    # Set the style with vertical grid lines\n",
    "    sns.set_style(\"whitegrid\", {'axes.grid.axis': 'x'})\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Drop missing values in 'OR_band'\n",
    "    df2023_updated = df2023.loc[df2023[\"OR_Band_3\"] != \"Missing\"]\n",
    "    \n",
    "     # Calculate the percentage of 'website' and 'no website' within each 'OR_band'\n",
    "    percentages = (\n",
    "        df2023_updated.groupby('OR_Band_3')['Website_Band']\n",
    "        .value_counts(normalize=True)\n",
    "        .unstack()\n",
    "        .fillna(0) * 100\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Ensure 'website' is displayed before 'no website'\n",
    "    percentages = percentages[['website', 'no website']]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Sort the revenue bands by the 'OR_band' labels in descending order\n",
    "    percentages = percentages.sort_index(ascending=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Plotting\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))\n",
    "    ax = plt.gca()\n",
    "    ax = percentages.plot(kind='barh', stacked=True, color=['#0b3d91', '#d3d3d3'], ax=ax, width=0.8)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Add labels and title\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('Percentage (%)')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('Revenue Bands (OR_band)')\n",
    "    plt.title('% of Websites of Firms by Revenue Bands')\n",
    "    plt.xlim(0, 100)\n",
    "    plt.legend(title='Website Band', loc='best')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Add percentages on bars for \"website\" part\n",
    "    for i, (index, row) in enumerate(percentages.iterrows()):\n",
    "        ax.text(row['website'] / 2, i, f\"{row['website']:.1f}%\", va='center', ha='center', color='white')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Show the plot\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example usage:\n",
    "plot_website_percentage_by_revenue(df2023)"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 48,
   "id": "108fa890-fde8-499b-bffa-c2bfac932cf9",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def filter_and_merge(df, category):\n",
    "    # Filter the dataframe by the specified category\n",
    "    filtered_df = df[df['CLUSTER_DEFN'] == category]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Further filter by REF_YR\n",
    "    filtered_df_2022 = filtered_df[(filtered_df['REF_YR'] == 2022)]\n",
    "    filtered_df_2023 = filtered_df[(filtered_df['REF_YR'] == 2023)]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Subset FINAL_IE = 'C' in 2023 but NOT 'C' in 2022\n",
    "    uen_2022_not_c = filtered_df_2022[filtered_df_2022['FINAL_IE'] != 'C']['UEN']\n",
    "    filtered_df_2023_c = filtered_df_2023[(filtered_df_2023['FINAL_IE'] == 'C') & \n",
    "                                          (filtered_df_2023['UEN'].isin(uen_2022_not_c))]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Load the CSV file to a dataframe\n",
    "    match_websites_df = pd.read_csv('datasets/ie2023_matchwebsites.csv')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Merge the dataframes on the 'UEN' column\n",
    "    merged_df = pd.merge(filtered_df_2023_c, match_websites_df, on='UEN', how='inner')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Select all columns from the match_websites_df and 'FINAL_IE' from the filtered_df_2023_c\n",
    "    result_df = merged_df[match_websites_df.columns.tolist() + ['FINAL_IE']]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return result_df, filtered_df_2023_c"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 49,
   "id": "8c6e4b32-633a-41c1-bdfe-84b08e6e6e8e",

   "source": [
    "def filter_uen_and_year(df, check_df):\n",
    "    # Filter df for UEN values that are in check_df\n",
    "    filtered_df = df[df['UEN'].isin(check_df['UEN'])]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Further filter for records where REF_YR is 2022\n",
    "    final_filtered_df = filtered_df[filtered_df['REF_YR'] == 2022]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return final_filtered_df"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "def update_df_based_on_check(df, check_df):\n",
    "    # Filter check_df for Age_Band not in '<= 5 Years'\n",
    "    filtered_check_df = check_df[check_df['Age_Band'] != '<= 5 Years']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Get UENs from the filtered check_df\n",
    "    uens_to_update = filtered_check_df['UEN']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Update df for REF_YR = 2022 where UENs match\n",
    "    df.loc[(df['UEN'].isin(uens_to_update)) & (df['REF_YR'] == 2022), ['FINAL_IE', 'IE_compare']] = ['C', 'website']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return df"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "#### Write-up on Percentage Change\n",
    "1. Most industries saw a huge increase in % change in firms with revenue-generating websites in 2022, & sustained an increase in % change in 2023. \n",
    "- Question: What is the most likely cause. Sources? Actual/True Increase? \n",
    "- Show % change in webscrapped sites over the years (emphasize on huge increase in 2022). \n",
    "- Zoom in on \"important industries\" & find reasonings. \n",
    "\n",
    "2. \"Real Estate\" saw a huge increase in % change in revenue-generating websites in 2023. \n",
    "- Many websites were generic property websites like \"Far East Organization\", \"99.co\", \"EdgeProp.sg\""
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "a52e6054-215a-4446-b3e0-ba17029afa9a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# count RE firms across years\n",
    "def count_re(df):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Group by CLUSTER_DEFN and REF_YR and count the occurrences\n",
    "    count_df = df.groupby(['CLUSTER_DEFN', 'REF_YR']).size().reset_index(name='Count')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Sort the DataFrame for better readability\n",
    "    count_df_re = count_df[count_df[\"CLUSTER_DEFN\"] == '18. Real Estate']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return count_df_re"
   ]
  },

   "id": "8a6eac6f-9210-433f-8887-15d58cdf8c1f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import duckdb\n",
    "from duckdb import sql\n",
    "\n",
    "re2023 = data.loc[(data[\"CLUSTER_DEFN\"] == '18. Real Estate') & (data[\"REF_YR\"] == 2023) & (data[\"FINAL_IE\"] == 'C')]\n",
    "\n",
    "merge_df = sql(\"\"\"\n",
    "SELECT\n",
    "   a.*, \n",
    "   b.WEBSITE\n",
    "FROM re2023 AS a \n",
    "INNER JOIN websites AS b \n",
    "ON a.UEN = b.UEN\n",
    "\"\"\").df()"
   ]
  },

    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filter data for enterprises with a corporate website\n",
    "IE_entp = data[data[\"IE_compare\"] == \"website\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Order the industries\n",
    "ordered_industries = sorted(IE_entp[\"CLUSTER_DEFN\"].unique())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filter data for the years of interest\n",
    "IE_entp_filtered = IE_entp[IE_entp['REF_YR'].isin([2020, 2021, 2022, 2023])]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a grid of plots\n",
    "g = sns.FacetGrid(\n",
    "    IE_entp_filtered, \n",
    "    col=\"REF_YR\", \n",
    "    col_wrap=2, \n",
    "    height=5, \n",
    "    aspect=1.5,\n",
    "    sharey=False\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Map the data to countplot\n",
    "g.map_dataframe(\n",
    "    sns.countplot, \n",
    "    y=\"CLUSTER_DEFN\", \n",
    "    hue=\"FINAL_IE\", \n",
    "    order=ordered_industries, \n",
    "    palette=\"viridis\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add titles and adjust layout\n",
    "g.set_axis_labels(\"Count\", \"Industry\")\n",
    "g.set_titles(col_template=\"{col_name}\")\n",
    "g.add_legend(title='FINAL_IE')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.9)\n",
    "g.fig.suptitle('Count of Enterprises with Corporate Website by Year and FINAL_IE')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "id": "4b2529ec-3123-4418-b52b-bda9c451afaa",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x1200 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot_enterprises_by_year(data):\n",
    "    # Filter data for enterprises with a corporate website\n",
    "    IE_entp = data[data[\"IE_compare\"] == \"website\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Order the industries\n",
    "    ordered_industries = sorted(IE_entp[\"CLUSTER_DEFN\"].unique())\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Create subplots\n",
    "    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 12), sharey=True)\n",
    "    years = [2020, 2021, 2022, 2023]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Plot each year in a separate subplot\n",
    "    for ax, year in zip(axes.flatten(), years):\n",
    "        year_data = IE_entp[IE_entp['REF_YR'] == year]\n",
    "        pivot_table = year_data.pivot_table(\n",
    "            index='CLUSTER_DEFN',\n",
    "            columns='FINAL_IE',\n",
    "            aggfunc='size',\n",
    "            fill_value=0\n",
    "        ).reindex(ordered_industries)\n",
    "\n",
    "        bottom = None\n",
    "        for ie in ['B', 'C']:\n",
    "            values = pivot_table[ie]\n",
    "            ax.barh(\n",
    "                pivot_table.index, \n",
    "                values, \n",
    "                left=bottom, \n",
    "                label=f'FINAL_IE {ie}'\n",
    "            )\n",
    "            if bottom is None:\n",
    "                bottom = values\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                bottom += values\n",
    "\n",
    "        ax.set_title(f'Year {year}')\n",
    "        ax.set_xlabel('Count')\n",
    "        ax.set_ylabel('Industry')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Add a legend to the first subplot\n",
    "    axes[0, 0].legend(title='FINAL_IE')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Adjust layout\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.suptitle('Count of Enterprises with Corporate Website by Year and FINAL_IE', y=1.02)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example usage\n",
    "plot_enterprises_by_year(data)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# Assuming 'data' is your DataFrame\n",
    "# Filter data for enterprises with websites and years 2022 and 2023\n",
    "IE_entp = data[(data[\"IE_compare\"] == \"website\") & (data[\"REF_YR\"].isin([2022, 2023]))]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a FacetGrid to separate plots by year\n",
    "g = sns.FacetGrid(IE_entp, col=\"REF_YR\", height=5, aspect=1.5, sharey=True, col_order=[2022, 2023])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Map a stacked bar plot to the grid\n",
    "g.map_dataframe(\n",
    "    sns.histplot, \n",
    "    y=\"CLUSTER_DEFN\", \n",
    "    hue=\"FINAL_IE\", \n",
    "    multiple=\"stack\", \n",
    "    palette=\"viridis\",\n",
    "    hue_order=sorted(IE_entp[\"FINAL_IE\"].unique())\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set titles and labels\n",
    "g.set_axis_labels('Count', 'Industry')\n",
    "g.set_titles(col_template='Year: {col_name}')\n",
    "g.add_legend(title='Website Type')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show plot\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# Assuming 'data' is your DataFrame\n",
    "# Filter data for enterprises with websites and years 2022 and 2023\n",
    "IE_entp = data[(data[\"IE_compare\"] == \"website\") & (data[\"REF_YR\"].isin([2022, 2023]))]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a FacetGrid to separate plots by year, using rows\n",
    "g = sns.FacetGrid(IE_entp, row=\"REF_YR\", height=5, aspect=2, sharex=True, row_order=[2022, 2023], legend_out=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Map a stacked bar plot to the grid with specified order\n",
    "g.map_dataframe(\n",
    "    sns.histplot, \n",
    "    y=\"CLUSTER_DEFN\", \n",
    "    hue=\"FINAL_IE\", \n",
    "    multiple=\"stack\", \n",
    "    palette=\"viridis\",\n",
    "    hue_order=[\"B\", \"C\"]  # Specify the order here\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set titles and labels\n",
    "g.set_axis_labels('Count', 'Industry')\n",
    "g.set_titles(row_template='Year: {row_name}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add legend for the hue variable\n",
    "g.add_legend(title='Website Type')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show plot\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

    "#### Industry Plots for Counts of Revenue Generating Websites across years (by industry): 2020 - 2023"

   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "data = data.loc[data[\"REF_YR\"].isin([2020, 2021, 2022, 2023])]\n",
    "\n",
    "# counts over industries (transpose)\n",
    "IE_entp = data[data[\"FINAL_IE\"] == \"C\"]\n",
    "# order = IE_entp[\"CLUSTER_DEFN\"].value_counts().index\n",
    "# Get the unique cluster definitions and sort them alphabetically\n",
    "order = sorted(IE_entp[\"CLUSTER_DEFN\"].unique())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a countplot with counts on the bars\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(16, 12))\n",
    "ax = sns.countplot(y=\"CLUSTER_DEFN\", data=IE_entp, hue=\"REF_YR\", palette=\"viridis\", order=order)\n",
    "\n",
    "for p in ax.patches:\n",
    "    ax.text(p.get_width() + 1, p.get_y() + p.get_height() / 2., \n",
    "            int(p.get_width()), \n",
    "            fontsize=11, color='black', ha='left', va='center')"
   ]

   "id": "aeaedfe2-e772-4afb-99c6-0219dbf79316",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_industry_plot(data):\n",
    "    import seaborn as sns\n",
    "    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "    import pandas as pd\n",
    "    '''Obtain subset of main industry plot for fluctuating trends.\n",
    "    '''\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Count of Enterprises with Corporate Website (by Industry)\n",
    "    IE_entp = data.loc[(data[\"FINAL_IE\"] == \"C\") & (data[\"CLUSTER_DEFN\"].isin([\"14. Accommodation\", \"17. Finance & Insurance\", \"15. Food & Beverage Services\"]))]\n",
    "    order = sorted(IE_entp[\"CLUSTER_DEFN\"].unique())\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 8))\n",
    "    sns.countplot(y=\"CLUSTER_DEFN\", data=IE_entp, hue=\"REF_YR\", palette=\"viridis\", order=order)\n",
    "    for p in plt.gca().patches:\n",
    "        plt.text(p.get_width() + 1, p.get_y() + p.get_height() / 2., \n",
    "                 int(p.get_width()), \n",
    "                 fontsize=12, color='black', ha='left', va='center')\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.title('Count of Enterprises with Revenue Generating Websites (by Selected Industries)')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('Count')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('Industry')"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def process_dataframes(data: pd.DataFrame, impute: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:\n",
    "    # Drop columns 'FINAL_IE' and 'Website_Band' from 'data'\n",
    "    data = data.drop(columns=['FINAL_IE', 'Website_Band'], errors='ignore')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Merge 'data' with 'impute' on 'UEN' and 'REF_YR'\n",
    "    merged_df = pd.merge(data, impute[['UEN', 'REF_YR', 'FINAL_IE', 'IE_compare']], \n",
    "                         on=['UEN', 'REF_YR'], how='inner')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Rename 'IE_compare' to 'Website_Band'\n",
    "    merged_df = merged_df.rename(columns={'IE_compare': 'Website_Band'})\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return merged_df"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data_or = sql(\"\"\"\n",
    "SELECT\n",
    "    a.*, \n",
    "    CASE\n",
    "        WHEN OR_Band in ('01. OR <= 1 Million', '02. 1 Million < OR <= 10 Million') THEN '1. Small Companies (OR <= 10 Million)'\n",
    "        WHEN OR_Band in ('03. 10 Million < OR <= 100 Million', OR_Band = '04. OR > 100 Million') THEN '2. Big Companies (OR > 10 Million)'\n",
    "        ELSE 'Missing'\n",
    "    END AS OR_breakdown\n",
    "    \n",
    "FROM data AS a\n",
    "\"\"\").df()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "# Calculate the proportions\n",
    "or_data = data_or.loc[(data_or[\"OR_breakdown\"] != 'Missing') & (data_or[\"REF_YR\"] == 2023) & (data_or[\"CLUSTER_DEFN\"] == '17. Finance & Insurance')]\n",
    "proportions = or_data.groupby('Revenue_Generating_Band')['OR_breakdown'].value_counts(normalize=True).rename('proportion').reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set the aesthetic style of the plots\n",
    "sns.set(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a bar plot with proportions\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "sns.barplot(data=proportions, x='Revenue_Generating_Band', y='proportion', hue='OR_breakdown')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add titles and labels\n",
    "plt.title('Proportion of OR Bands for Firms with Revenue-Generating Websites vs Firms with No Revenue-Generating Websites')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Firms with Revenue-Generating Websites vs Firms with No Revenue-Generating Websites')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Proportion')\n",
    "plt.legend(title='Operating Revenue Bands')"
   ]

   "source": [
    "# Derive vars productivity and profit_margin\n",
    "# Calculate PROFIT_MARGIN\n",
    "merged_df['PROFIT_MARGIN'] = merged_df['FLAD_PROFIT'] / merged_df['FLAD_OR']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate productivity\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate productivity, avoiding division by zero\n",
    "merged_df['productivity'] = np.where(\n",
    "    merged_df['ADJ_TOT_EMP'] != 0,\n",
    "    merged_df['FLAD_VA'] / merged_df['ADJ_TOT_EMP'],\n",
    "    np.nan\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "merged_df.head()"
   ]
  },

   "id": "a714ce50-c18b-462a-accc-193019adfd54",

    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy.stats import ttest_ind, t\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Assuming merged_df is your DataFrame\n",
    "# Separate the data into two groups based on the Revenue_Generating_Band\n",
    "group1 = merged_df[merged_df['Revenue_Generating_Band'] == 'Non Revenue Generating']['productivity'].dropna()\n",
    "group2 = merged_df[merged_df['Revenue_Generating_Band'] == 'Revenue Generating']['productivity'].dropna()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Conduct the t-test for a right-tailed test\n",
    "t_stat, p_value = ttest_ind(group2, group1, equal_var=False, alternative='greater')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Degrees of freedom\n",
    "df = len(group1) + len(group2) - 2\n",
    "\n",
    "# Critical value for a right-tailed test\n",
    "alpha = 0.05\n",
    "critical_value = t.ppf(1 - alpha, df)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plotting the t-distribution\n",
    "x = np.linspace(-4, 4, 1000)\n",
    "y = t.pdf(x, df)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(x, y, label='t-distribution', color='blue')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fill critical region\n",
    "plt.fill_between(x, y, where=(x > critical_value), color='red', alpha=0.5, label='Critical Region')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the t-statistic\n",
    "plt.axvline(t_stat, color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'T-statistic = {t_stat:.2f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Labels and legend\n",
    "plt.title('T-Distribution with Critical Region')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('T-value')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Density')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Annotate the p-value\n",
    "plt.annotate(f'P-value = {p_value:.4f}', xy=(t_stat, 0.1), xytext=(t_stat+0.5, 0.15),\n",
    "             arrowprops=dict(facecolor='black', arrowstyle='->'))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy.stats import ttest_ind, t\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Assuming df_or is your DataFrame\n",
    "# Separate the data into two groups based on the Revenue_Generating_Band\n",
    "group1 = merged_df[merged_df['Website_Band'] == 'no website']['productivity'].dropna()\n",
    "group2 = merged_df[merged_df['Website_Band'] == 'website']['productivity'].dropna()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Conduct the t-test\n",
    "t_stat, p_value = ttest_ind(group1, group2, equal_var=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Degrees of freedom\n",
    "df = len(group1) + len(group2) - 2\n",
    "\n",
    "# Critical values for a two-tailed test\n",
    "alpha = 0.05\n",
    "critical_value = t.ppf(1 - alpha/2, df)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plotting the t-distribution\n",
    "x = np.linspace(-4, 4, 1000)\n",
    "y = t.pdf(x, df)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(x, y, label='t-distribution', color='blue')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fill critical regions\n",
    "plt.fill_between(x, y, where=(x < -critical_value), color='red', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "plt.fill_between(x, y, where=(x > critical_value), color='red', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the t-statistic\n",
    "plt.axvline(t_stat, color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'T-statistic = {t_stat:.2f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Labels and legend\n",
    "plt.title('T-Distribution with Critical Regions')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('T-value')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Density')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Annotate the p-value\n",
    "plt.annotate(f'P-value = {p_value:.4f}', xy=(t_stat, 0.1), xytext=(t_stat+0.5, 0.15),\n",
    "             arrowprops=dict(facecolor='black', arrowstyle='->'))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Assuming merged_df is already defined\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate average productivity by Website_Band and convert to thousands\n",
    "average_productivity = merged_df.groupby('Website_Band')['productivity'].mean() / 1000\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reorder the index to display \"website\" first\n",
    "average_productivity = average_productivity.reindex(['website', 'no website'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the bar chart with reduced gap\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 6))\n",
    "bars = plt.bar(average_productivity.index, average_productivity.values, color=['#0b3d91', '#d3d3d3'], width=0.6)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add labels and title\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Website Band')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Average Productivity (\\'000)')\n",
    "plt.title('Average Productivity of Firms with and without Websites')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add average productivity on top of each bar\n",
    "for bar in bars:\n",
    "    yval = bar.get_height()\n",
    "    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, yval, f'{yval:.1f}', ha='center', va='bottom')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show the plot\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=0)  # Keep x labels horizontal\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy.stats import ttest_ind\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plotting the boxplot using seaborn\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 7))\n",
    "sns.boxplot(x='Revenue_Generating_Band', y='FLAD_OR', data=df_or, palette=\"viridis\", showfliers=False)\n",
    "plt.title('OR Distributions by Revenue Generating Band')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Revenue Generating Band')\n",

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 114,
   "id": "68d048a1-2c5c-46a3-a91d-9c6e23a70edb",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "T-statistic: -2.6354498730320985\n",
      "P-value: 0.00840399954190945\n",
      "There is a statistically significant difference between the means of the two groups.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Performing the t-test\n",
    "df_or_clean = df_or.dropna(subset=[\"FLAD_OR\"])\n",
    "# Separate the data into two groups based on the Revenue_Generating_Band\n",
    "group1 = df_or_clean[df_or_clean['Revenue_Generating_Band'] == 'Non Revenue Generating']['FLAD_OR']\n",
    "group2 = df_or_clean[df_or_clean['Revenue_Generating_Band'] == 'Revenue Generating']['FLAD_OR']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Conduct the t-test\n",
    "t_stat, p_value = ttest_ind(group1, group2, equal_var=False)  # Use equal_var=False for Welch's t-test\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print the results\n",
    "print(f\"T-statistic: {t_stat}\")\n",
    "print(f\"P-value: {p_value}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Interpretation\n",
    "alpha = 0.05\n",
    "if p_value < alpha:\n",
    "    print(\"There is a statistically significant difference between the means of the two groups.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"There is no statistically significant difference between the means of the two groups.\")"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 144,
   "id": "951e8912-775d-46ae-b111-0303bf88fcd1",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy.stats import ttest_ind, t\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Assuming merged_df is your DataFrame\n",
    "# Separate the data into two groups based on the Revenue_Generating_Band\n",
    "group1 = merged_df[merged_df['Revenue_Generating_Band'] == 'Non Revenue Generating']['FLAD_OR'].dropna()\n",
    "group2 = merged_df[merged_df['Revenue_Generating_Band'] == 'Revenue Generating']['FLAD_OR'].dropna()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Conduct the t-test for a right-tailed test\n",
    "t_stat, p_value = ttest_ind(group2, group1, equal_var=False, alternative='greater')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Degrees of freedom\n",
    "df = len(group1) + len(group2) - 2\n",
    "\n",
    "# Critical value for a right-tailed test\n",
    "alpha = 0.05\n",
    "critical_value = t.ppf(1 - alpha, df)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plotting the t-distribution\n",
    "x = np.linspace(-4, 4, 1000)\n",
    "y = t.pdf(x, df)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(x, y, label='t-distribution', color='blue')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fill critical region\n",
    "plt.fill_between(x, y, where=(x > critical_value), color='red', alpha=0.5, label='Critical Region')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the t-statistic\n",
    "plt.axvline(t_stat, color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'T-statistic = {t_stat:.2f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Labels and legend\n",
    "plt.title('T-Distribution with Critical Region')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('T-value')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Density')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Annotate the p-value\n",
    "plt.annotate(f'P-value = {p_value:.4f}', xy=(t_stat, 0.1), xytext=(t_stat+0.5, 0.15),\n",
    "             arrowprops=dict(facecolor='black', arrowstyle='->'))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 112,
   "id": "d25c8f0a-f1b3-4564-88b7-02ab1697f897",
   "metadata": {

   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array(['Non Revenue Generating', 'Revenue Generating'], dtype=object)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 112,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }

    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy.stats import ttest_ind\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plotting the boxplot using seaborn\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n",
    "sns.boxplot(x='Revenue_Generating_Band', y='FLAD_PROFIT', data=df_or, palette=\"viridis\", showfliers=False)\n",
    "plt.title('Profit Distributions by Revenue Generating Band')\n",

    "plt.ylabel('FLAD_PROFIT')\n",
    "plt.xticks()\n",

   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 122,
   "id": "3cc6009f-b5fb-491a-91fa-a2687a3f3adb",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy.stats import ttest_ind, t\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Separate the data into two groups based on the Revenue_Generating_Band\n",
    "group1 = df_or[df_or['Revenue_Generating_Band'] == 'Non Revenue Generating']['FLAD_PROFIT'].dropna()\n",
    "group2 = df_or[df_or['Revenue_Generating_Band'] == 'Revenue Generating']['FLAD_PROFIT'].dropna()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Conduct the t-test\n",
    "t_stat, p_value = ttest_ind(group1, group2, equal_var=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Degrees of freedom\n",
    "df = len(group1) + len(group2) - 2\n",
    "\n",
    "# Critical values for a two-tailed test\n",
    "alpha = 0.05\n",
    "critical_value = t.ppf(1 - alpha/2, df)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plotting the t-distribution\n",
    "x = np.linspace(-4, 4, 1000)\n",
    "y = t.pdf(x, df)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(x, y, label='t-distribution', color='blue')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fill critical regions\n",
    "plt.fill_between(x, y, where=(x < -critical_value), color='red', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "plt.fill_between(x, y, where=(x > critical_value), color='red', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the t-statistic\n",
    "plt.axvline(t_stat, color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'T-statistic = {t_stat:.2f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Labels and legend\n",
    "plt.title('T-Distribution with Critical Regions for FLAD_PROFIT')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('T-value')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Density')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Annotate the p-value\n",
    "plt.annotate(f'P-value = {p_value:.4f}', xy=(t_stat, 0.1), xytext=(t_stat+0.5, 0.15),\n",
    "             arrowprops=dict(facecolor='black', arrowstyle='->'))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# get bc df (take all*)\n",
    "data_bc = data[data[\"REF_YR\"] == 2023]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the percentages of \"website\" and \"no website\" for each year and IE_compare\n",
    "percentages = data_bc.groupby(\"NSME_IND\")[\"Website_Band\"].value_counts(normalize=True).apply(lambda x: x * 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Pivot the data to create a DataFrame with the years as the columns and the \"website\" and \"no website\" as the index\n",
    "df_pivot = percentages.unstack().reindex(columns=[\"website\", \"no website\"]).sort_values(by=\"website\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a stacked bar plot of the percentages using matplotlib\n",
    "ax = df_pivot.plot(kind=\"barh\", stacked=True, cmap='tab20b', width=0.6, figsize=(12, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set the title and axis labels\n",
    "plt.title(\"Share of Enterprises with Website by NSME/SME Status, 2022\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Percentage\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"NSME Status\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Move the legend outside the plot\n",
    "ax.legend(loc=\"upper left\", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Turn on percentage labels on the bars\n",
    "for patch in ax.patches:\n",
    "    width, height = patch.get_width(), patch.get_height()\n",
    "    x, y = patch.get_xy()\n",
    "    if width > 0 and (patch.get_label() != \"no website\" or patch.get_x() > 0):\n",
    "        ax.text(x + width/2, y + height/2, f\"{width:.1f}%\", ha=\"center\", va=\"center\", color=\"white\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "70fe50bd-0792-4029-b5ab-7748653ccd64",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filter the data for the year 2023\n",
    "data_bc = data[data[\"REF_YR\"] == 2023]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the percentages of FINAL_IE categories for each NSME_IND\n",
    "percentages = (\n",
    "    data_bc.groupby(\"NSME_IND\")[\"FINAL_IE\"]\n",
    "    .value_counts(normalize=True)\n",
    "    .unstack(fill_value=0)\n",
    "    .mul(100)\n",
    "    .reindex(columns=[\"A\", \"B\", \"C\"])\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define a dark blue color palette\n",
    "colors = ['#4f8bc9', '#2e4053', '#1b2631']  # Brighter for A, toned for B and C\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a stacked bar plot of the percentages using matplotlib\n",
    "ax = percentages.plot(kind=\"barh\", stacked=True, color=colors, width=0.6, figsize=(12, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set the title and axis labels\n",
    "plt.title(\"Share of IE Categories by NSME/SME Status, 2023\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Percentage\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"NSME Status\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Move the legend outside the plot\n",
    "ax.legend(loc=\"upper left\", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add percentage labels on the bars\n",
    "for patch in ax.patches:\n",
    "    width = patch.get_width()\n",
    "    if width > 0:\n",
    "        ax.text(patch.get_x() + width / 2, patch.get_y() + patch.get_height() / 2,\n",
    "                f\"{width:.1f}%\", ha=\"center\", va=\"center\", color=\"white\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

     "execution_count": 15,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def update_nsme_ind(df):\n",
    "    # Create a mapping of UEN to NSME_IND for the year 2022\n",
    "    uen_nsme_map = df[df[\"REF_YR\"] == 2022].set_index(\"UEN\")[\"NSME_IND\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Update NSME_IND for the year 2023 using the mapping\n",
    "    df.loc[df[\"REF_YR\"] == 2023, \"NSME_IND\"] = df[df[\"REF_YR\"] == 2023][\"UEN\"].map(uen_nsme_map)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Convert NSME_IND to integer, handling NaN values\n",
    "    df[\"NSME_IND\"] = df[\"NSME_IND\"].fillna(0).astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example usage:\n",
    "df3 = update_nsme_ind(df2)\n",
    "df4 = df3.loc[df3[\"REF_YR\"] == 2023]\n",
    "df4[\"NSME_IND\"].value_counts()"
   ]
  },
